{
    "description_long": "This object consists of a row of seven distinct grave markers, each resembling a traditional tombstone or headstone, arranged side by side. The markers vary in shape, with some featuring rounded tops, others flat, and one with a broken or jagged edge, suggesting age or damage. The surfaces are textured to mimic weathered stone, with subtle color variations ranging from gray to mossy green, indicating exposure to the elements. The bases of the markers are slightly raised, and the overall forms are blocky and solid, typical of stone memorials found in graveyards. No visible inscriptions or engravings are present on the surfaces, and there are no decorative elements such as crosses or statues. The set is representative of a small section of a cemetery, suitable for urban parks or memorial sites.",
